parameters: ...There's not really anything special here. \n< Suspicious tool shop >
Welcome. Oh my, what brings a young lady like you to
our store? \n< Suspicious tool shop >
I was asked by someone to deliver a
special...something, shall I say. Anyway, I came to
deliver it. \n< Serena >
Oh, it's you. Yes, we handle that item in our store.
Please take it. \n< Suspicious tool shop >
This...child... \n< Serena >
Oh my, oh my. This is a plump and healthy little
baby. Yes, yes, it already has teeth. These claws look
like they could yield some good materials. \n< Suspicious tool shop >
\n< Serena >
The eyeballs have a beautiful shape. The shape of the
skull is also good with a broad occipital bone. The
quality of the mother must have been good. \n< Suspicious tool shop >
Um...there's something off about this. What will
happen to that child? What does she intend to do? \n< Serena >
What use could there be for goblins or baby monsters?
There can only be one. \n< Suspicious tool shop >
...Ah! Of course, human infants would be preferable.
However, that's not possible here. It would be
troublesome. As expected, the city wouldn't stay
silent about it. \n< Suspicious tool shop >
Yes, for our shop, monster infants are sufficient. We
are able to meet the demand. Yes. \n< Suspicious tool shop >
So, if you could bring me a high-quality one that was
just born and is still alive, I would really
appreciate it. \n< Suspicious tool shop >
We adventurers have a mutually beneficial
relationship, so please feel free to support us too,
on this occasion. \n< Suspicious tool shop >
So, in return, take this. \n< Suspicious tool shop >
Is this... a healing potion? \n< Serena >
The effectiveness is slightly inferior compared to
something derived from magic, but well... \n< Suspicious tool shop >
Potion... I wonder if it has any effect on physical
discomfort...? If I bring it back and make her drink
it, that woman might calm down a little. \n< Serena >
...I understand. I'll take it. \n< Serena >
If you are also in trouble with a monster baby, please
come visit us. Instead of cash, we will return the
favor with a special item. \n< Suspicious tool shop >
I don't think I'll come back again. \n< Serena >
Let's head back to the guild for now. \n< Serena >
Welcome to the magic tool shop. Our practicality can
compete with even the tool shops on the main street. \n< Suspicious tool shop >
Oh, a guest. What brings you here today?
I came for shopping.
Please adopt a child of a monster.

Well well, Serena, do you need anything? \n< Andre >
I'm in trouble because I've been parasitized by a
slime. I'm sorry, could you give me some medicine? \n< Serena >
Hahaha, a sewer slime? Yes, of course, that's fine.
Sorry, but would it be possible for you to bring some
of the slime in a jar? \n< Andre >
You, don't humiliate me like that...ugh! \n< Serena >
You seem to be in pain. However, I'm not a charity,
so... What would you like me to do? \n< Andre >
... Alright. Since I understand, please give me that
medicine. \n< Serena >
The negotiations have succeeded. The restroom is
located in the back, so please feel free to use it. \n< Andre >
...Ugh. \n< Serena >
(The scene fades to black, followed by Serena's slime
discharge.)
(...This is such a dirty and despicable way to do
things. At this rate, I will be no better than the man
I caught...) \n< Serena >
So this is the infamous slime... Hmmm. \n< Andre >
Oh, don't stare too much...It's something that came
out of my body. \n< Serena >
Oh, excuse me. But to gaze at what has come out of
Serena's body, I've done it many times before. \n< Andre >
\n< Serena >
Oh, I apologize again. Here is the slime remover. When
used, it will quickly expel all slime from the body,
so please use it in a safe place. \n< Andre >
...That's a relief. \n< Serena >
If it's okay with you, please bring more slimes next
time. \n< Andre >
\n< Serena >
